answers.body_markdown:
If you only have a fid, you need to load the file.

```php
use \Drupal\file\Entity\File;

$fid = 123; // Your fid   
$file = File::load($fid);
```

From there, you can use the [getFileUri][1] method to get the URI. If you want to get the complete URL, you can use the [file_create_url][2] function.

```php
$uri = $file-&gt;getFileUri();
// You get : public://directory/file.jpg
$url = file_create_url($uri);
// You get : http://mywebsite.com/sites/default/files/directory/file.jpg
```

  [1]: https://api.drupal.org/api/drupal/core%21modules%21file%21src%21Entity%21File.php/function/File%3A%3AgetFileUri/8.2.x
  [2]: https://api.drupal.org/api/drupal/core%21includes%21file.inc/function/file_create_url/8.2.x

