All `zmq_*` functions will return an error and set errno. Check every function and `break` when an error occur. In that scenario, polling on non-blocking function is best to `break` out of your `while`loop when an error occurs.

On Linux, you can also set a signal handler and execute a clean up routine when a singal is raised (for example, it is very common to catch SIGINT to properly exit a program on UNIX on ctrl+C in the console).  See this [answer](https://stackoverflow.com/questions/55508391/zeromq-handling-interrupt-in-multithreaded-application/55512521#55512521)

